1. #include <stdio.h> is a header file library for input/output functions
2. double variable in order to represent the data of multiple numbers
   (decimals, negative values, etc. etc.)
3. printf function to show the user where they will input the numbers and
   to print out results
4. scanf function to scan and read data of the given number
5. %lf refers to the given numbers
6. %num refers to a specific number
7. if statement was only added to identify the largest number
8. the quotations in the if is the deciding factor whether the specific
   number that was given is the largest or not
9. %.2f to limit on how many numbers in the decimal can be shown.
   In this case, it's only 2.
10. return 0 to end the function

